prompts.template:
/BOOT @GitHub

Department: {department}
{custom_block}

/ADVISORY @GitHub

Target Department: {department}

Draft a concise advisory using the canonical source-board plus Advisory Index workflow. Do not post or change durable advisory state unless I explicitly say to send or implement it.
{custom_block}

/SYNCADVISORY @GitHub

Read the Advisory Index and relevant boards. Report open, stale, duplicate, or inconsistent advisory state. Do not make changes.
{custom_block}

/ITINERARY @Todoist @Google Calendar

Review today's calendar, Todoist tasks, overdue items, and known priorities. Produce a practical daily itinerary with time-sensitive commitments first, realistic task blocks, and a short list of what matters most. Do not change Todoist or Calendar unless I explicitly authorize changes.
{custom_block}

/TODOIST @Todoist

Review the current conversation and identify the exact Todoist task changes needed. Add, update, complete, reschedule, move, or review tasks only as authorized. Ask for clarification when project, date, time, or task identity is ambiguous. Report exactly what changed and what remains unresolved.
{custom_block}

/MORNING @GitHub

Department: {department}

Run the canonical read-only boot and sync sequence for this department. Then provide a concise morning report covering today's priorities, calendar or task pressures when relevant, open loops, advisories, blockers, and the single best next action. Do not modify GitHub or external systems unless I explicitly authorize it.
{custom_block}

/NIGHTLY @GitHub

Department: {department}

Run the canonical read-only boot and synchronization sequence for this department. Review completed work, unfinished loops, stale documentation, advisory state, blockers, and the next handoff needed. Do not modify GitHub or external systems unless I explicitly authorize it.
{custom_block}

/OPENLOOPS @GitHub

Department: {department}

Read the relevant handoff and open-loop files. Separate active, waiting, blocked, stale, and recently closed items. Recommend the smallest useful next actions without changing durable state.
{custom_block}

/CAPTURE @GitHub

Classify the raw thought or note below. Recommend the correct destination: GitHub durable memory, a project notebook, an open loop, Todoist, Calendar, Google Drive, or no capture. Do not write anything until I explicitly authorize the destination and change.
{custom_block}

/DRIVE @Google Drive

Work only with the requested Google Drive, Docs, Sheets, or Slides task. Confirm the target file or folder, use small verified operations, and report the exact result. Do not make unrelated changes.
{custom_block}

/CALENDAR @Google Calendar

Review or prepare the requested Calendar operation with timezone-aware details. Inspect conflicts before proposing changes, and do not create, move, or cancel events unless I explicitly authorize it.
{custom_block}

/GMAIL @Gmail

Search and summarize only the requested Gmail evidence. Extract decisions, unanswered messages, deadlines, and follow-up actions. Draft replies when useful, but do not send, archive, delete, or label messages without explicit authorization.
{custom_block}
